{
  "name": "Run FSM Approval Regression Tests",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Complete approval regression testing workflow: Parse TES-070, Generate JSON, Execute tests, Generate report. Triggers invoice-approval-test-agent for autonomous execution.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "UNIVERSAL FSM APPROVAL REGRESSION TESTING WORKFLOW\n\nThis hook orchestrates the complete approval testing workflow and delegates execution to specialized subagents.\n\nPHASE 1: GATHER INFORMATION\n1. List clients in Projects/ - user selects\n2. List TES-070 documents in Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Approval_TES070s_For_Regression_Testing/ - user selects\n3. Prompt for FSM credentials (URL, username, password, environment)\n4. Save credentials to Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials/ (.env.fsm and .env.passwords)\n\nPHASE 2: PARSE TES-070 AND DETECT TRANSACTION TYPE\n5. Run: python ReusableTools/tes070_analyzer.py \"<tes070_path>\"\n6. Read the generated _analysis.json file\n7. Extract transaction type from analysis (ExpenseInvoice, ManualJournal, CashLedgerTransaction)\n8. Map transaction type to specialized subagent:\n   - ExpenseInvoice -> invoice-approval-test-agent\n   - ManualJournal -> journal-approval-test-agent (NOT YET CREATED)\n   - CashLedgerTransaction -> cash-approval-test-agent (NOT YET CREATED)\n\nPHASE 3: VALIDATE SUBAGENT EXISTS\n9. Check if required subagent exists in .kiro/agents/\n10. If subagent does NOT exist:\n    - Display error: \"Transaction type {type} requires {agent-name} which is not yet created\"\n    - List available agents\n    - Stop execution\n    - Suggest: Create the required subagent or use a different TES-070 document\n11. If subagent exists: Continue to Phase 4\n\nPHASE 4: GENERATE EXECUTABLE JSON SCENARIOS\n12. Create EXECUTABLE JSON scenario file with proper action definitions\n13. Use TES-070 analysis to understand test scenarios\n14. Generate JSON with actions: mcp_playwright_browser_navigate, mcp_playwright_browser_click, mcp_playwright_browser_type, mcp_playwright_browser_snapshot, mcp_playwright_browser_take_screenshot\n15. Save to: Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/{extension_id}_executable_scenarios.json\n16. Validate JSON using: python ReusableTools/validate_json.py\n\nPHASE 5: INVOKE SPECIALIZED TESTING SUBAGENT\n17. Invoke subagent with prompt:\n    \"Execute approval tests for {ClientName} using:\n    - TES-070 Analysis: {analysis_json_path}\n    - Executable Scenarios: {executable_json_path}\n    - FSM URL: {url}\n    - Username: {username}\n    - Password: {password}\n    - Environment: {environment}\n    \n    Use MCP Playwright tools to:\n    1. Navigate FSM UI\n    2. Create and submit invoices\n    3. Perform approvals/rejections\n    4. Capture screenshots at each step\n    5. Generate TES-070 report with evidence\"\n\n18. Subagent executes tests autonomously using MCP Playwright\n19. Subagent generates TES-070 document\n\nPHASE 6: DISPLAY SUMMARY\n20. Show final summary with pass/fail counts, TES-070 path, evidence location\n\nCURRENTLY AVAILABLE AGENTS:\n- invoice-approval-test-agent: Handles ExpenseInvoice approval workflows (Payables module)\n\nFUTURE AGENTS (Not yet created):\n- journal-approval-test-agent: Will handle ManualJournal approval workflows (GL module)\n- cash-approval-test-agent: Will handle CashLedgerTransaction approval workflows (Cash module)\n\nCRITICAL: The subagent MUST use MCP Playwright tools directly (mcp_playwright_browser_*), NOT the Python testing framework.\n\nExecute this workflow now."
  },
  "enabled": true
}
